cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY 

The paper deals with analyzing a large dataset of research papers and review reports to improve the peer-review system. The analysis involves creating a reviewer-reviewer interaction network and using its structural properties to predict the long-term citations of a submitted paper. This falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), software development (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY).
